<c74object name='av.pix.chromakey' category='' module=''>

    <digest>
        Use chromakeying to create a transparent background
    </digest>

    <description>
        Apply a chromakeying effect, where the selected color is removed from the image, leaving a transparent spot. The av.pix.chromakey is based on the co.chromakey.hsv.jxs code. But instead of already blending 2 textures (where one is chromakeyed and the other is used as background), this object outputs a single texture with the alpha channel being part of the chromakeying.
    </description>
    
    <discussion>
        
    </discussion>

